					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Opcodes that a 4 Mhz 65816 would be faster than a 8 Mhz 68000 would be:<br /><br />-branching<br />-shifting by less than 3<br />-shifting by 8<br />-ALU and load/store instructions that use immediate, absolute or indexed addressing (except when &quot;clc&quot; and &quot;sec&quot; are needed)<br />-non-word aligned memory accesses<br /><br />Opcodes 8 Mhz 68000 is faster at:<br /><br />-shifting by more than 3 but less than 8<br />-ALU and load/store instructions that use registers or register indirect addressing<br />-ALU instructions that require &quot;clc&quot; or &quot;sec&quot;<br />-32-bit ALU instructions</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

